# Frontend-Specific Rules - Johannes Wild Portfolio

## Next.js 14 App Router Patterns

### File Structure
```
app/
├── layout.tsx          # Root layout (metadata, fonts, providers)
├── page.tsx           # Home page (single-page portfolio)
├── globals.css        # Global styles & Tailwind imports
└── template.tsx       # (Optional) Page transition wrapper

components/
├── sections/          # Page sections
│   ├── HeroSection.tsx
│   ├── AboutSection.tsx
│   ├── SkillsSection.tsx
│   ├── ExperienceSection.tsx
│   ├── ProjectsSection.tsx
│   └── ContactSection.tsx
├── ui/                # Reusable UI components
│   ├── Button.tsx
│   ├── Card.tsx
│   ├── SkillBar.tsx
│   └── SectionTitle.tsx
└── layout/            # Layout components
    ├── Header.tsx
    ├── Footer.tsx
    └── Navigation.tsx

lib/
├── sanity.ts          # Sanity client & queries
├── utils.ts           # Helper functions
└── types.ts           # TypeScript types
```

### Server vs Client Components

**Use Server Components (default) for:**
- Layout structure
- Data fetching from Sanity
- Static content rendering
- SEO-critical content

**Use Client Components ('use client') for:**
- Animations (Framer Motion)
- Interactive elements (forms, buttons with state)
- Event handlers (onClick, onChange, etc.)
- Hooks (useState, useEffect, useReducedMotion, etc.)
- Browser-only APIs

### Example Server Component (Data Fetching)
```typescript
// app/page.tsx
import { client, queries } from '@/lib/sanity';
import HeroSection from '@/components/sections/HeroSection';

export default async function Home() {
  // Fetch data on the server
  const profile = await client.fetch(queries.profile);
  const projects = await client.fetch(queries.projects);
  const skills = await client.fetch(queries.skills);
  const experience = await client.fetch(queries.experience);

  return (
    <main className="relative">
      <HeroSection profile={profile} />
      {/* Pass data to client components as props */}
    </main>
  );
}
```

